The '''Commando Blindé du Cambodge''' ("Cambodia Armored Commando") was a military formation during the [[French Protectorate of Cambodia]]. The ad-hoc unit consisted of 11 commandeered [[Japanese tanks of World War II|Japanese tank]]s, some [[Renault UE Chenillette]] tankettes, and Ford trucks.<ref name="défenseVaïsse1998">{{cite book|author1=Centre d'étude d'histoire de la défense|author2=Maurice Vaïsse|title=La IVe Republique face aux problemes d'armement: actes du colloque organisé les 29 et 30 septembre 1997, à l'Ecole militaire|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o3ffAAAAMAAJ|year=1998|publisher=ADDIM|isbn=978-2-907341-63-9|page=320}}</ref>

