'''Klaipėda Chamber Orchestra''' ({{lang-lt|Klaipėdos kamerinis orkestras}}) is a [[chamber orchestra]] in the [[Lithuania]]n city of [[Klaipėda]]. It was founded in 1992 by violist Liuda Kuraitienė, who remained orchestra's artistic director.<ref name=kmh/> In June 2009, she was succeeded by cellist Mindaugas Bačkus. Over the years, the orchestra delivered over 400 concerts and participated in various domestic and international music festivals.<ref name=kmh/> The orchestra also organizes ''Playful Music Orchestra'', an educational program that allow schoolchildren to perform with professionals.<ref name=kl/>

