{{Infobox school |name = Lycée Français de Riga |native_name = Rīgas Franču licejs |latin_name = |logo = |seal_image = |image = RFL.png |image size = 200px |caption = Riga French Lyceum [[seal (emblem)|seal]] |motto = [[Liberté, égalité, fraternité]] |motto_translation = Freedom, equality, brotherhood |streetaddress = Mēness iela 8 |city = [[Riga]] |county = |postalcode = LV-1013 |country = {{flagicon|Latvia}} [[Latvia]] |coordinates = {{coord|56|58|0.24|N|24|8|14.71|E|type:edu_region:LV|display=inline,title}} |type = Public |established = |founded = |opened = September 1921 |founder = |principal = Vineta Rūtenberga |staff = |teaching_staff = |grades = 1 to 12 |lower_age = 7 |upper_age = 19 |age range = |pupils = |enrollment_as_of = |classes = |avg_class_size = |language = Latvian, French |classrooms = |colors = Royal blue, white, and red | publication = |slogan = |song = |sports = |mascot = |mascot image = |nickname = |team_name = |national_ranking = |alumni = |website = [http://www.rfl.lv rfl.lv] |footnotes = }}
The '''Riga French Lyceum''' ({{lang-lv|Rīgas Franču licejs}}, {{lang-fr|Lycée Français de Riga}}) is a [[:category:French international schools|French international school]] that was founded in September 1921 in [[Riga]], [[Latvia]].<ref>[http://www.rfl.lv/ Lycée Français de Riga official site]</ref> It is a school, where studies take place from grade 1 to 12 and the only school in Latvia, where [[French language|French]] can be learned at an advanced level starting from primary school. Studies can also be commenced in grade 7 or 10.
==History== Marsels Etjēns Segrests, the former Director of the Lycée Marsels, was one of the first teachers at the school. In addition to teaching French he also taught the [[Latvian language]] and literature. He was joined by Angelika Gailīte, a history teacher. It was located at Krisjana Valdemara street.
In 1965 the school was renamed as the [[Henri Barbusse]] Riga 11th secondary school. At this time it was located at 8 Meness Street, Riga. On 21 September 1991 the original name, Lycée Français de Riga, was restored.
==See also== *[[List_of_international_schools#France|List of French International Schools]] *[[Tallinn French School|Lycée Francais de Tallinn]]
