The '''''Lycée français [[Antoine de Saint-Exupéry|Saint Exupéry]]''''' is a French international school in [[Ouagadougou]], [[Burkina Faso]]. 

It serves levels ''maternelle'' (preschool) through ''lycée'' (senior high school). It was established in 1975.<ref>"[http://www.ambafrance-bf.org/Lycee-Saint-Exupery Ouagadougou : Lycée français Saint Exupery]." Embassy of France in Burkina Faso. Retrieved on 19 January 2015.</ref> The secondary school is in the centre of the city while the primary school is in proximity to the ''hôtel Indépendance''.<ref name=Embassypage2016>"[http://www.ambafrance-bf.org/Ouagadougou-Ecole-et-lycee-francais-Saint-Exupery Ouagadougou : Ecole et lycée français Saint Exupery]." Embassy of France in Burkina Faso. Retrieved on 10 July 2016.</ref>

{{Asof|2016}} there are about 125 employees and 1,000 students.<ref name=Embassypage2016/>

