'''Napoleon Barleycorn''' was  a [[Primitive Methodist]] [[missionary]] in [[Spanish Guinea]],  a [[Fernandinos#II. Fernandinos .28Krios.29|Fernandino]] of [[Igbo people|Igbo]] descent,<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_csii76oqg4C&pg=PA149|title=From Slaving to Neoslavery: The Bight of Biafra and Fernando Po in the Era of Abolition, 1827-1930|last=Sundiata|first=I. K.|date=1996|publisher=Univ of Wisconsin Press|year=|isbn=9780299145101|location=|pages=149|language=en}}</ref> who sent his sons to be educated at [[Bourne College]] in [[Quinton, Birmingham|Quinton]], [[England]]. One of his sons was [[William N Barleycorn|William Napoleon Barleycorn]], the well-known writer of the first [[Bube language]] primer.

